        "subject": "LU-16572 lnet: change allocation to atomic for udsp",
        "message": "LU-16572 lnet: change allocation to atomic for udsp\n\nTesting of UDSP shows the following backtrace:\n\nCall Trace:\n? dump_stack+0xbb/0x10e\n? ___might_sleep.cold.92+0xd9/0x107\n? __might_sleep+0x59/0xc0\n? slab_pre_alloc_hook.constprop.64+0x11f/0x1d0\n? kmem_cache_alloc_trace+0x5b/0x440\n? snprintf+0x51/0x70\n? lnet_udsp_info_send+0x5c/0x5e0 [lnet]\n? __nla_reserve+0x48/0x60\n? lnet_net_show_dump+0x65e/0x1bc0 [lnet]\n\nMake the memory allocation atomic.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-lnet\nFixes: d15bfca0785 (\"LU-10391 lnet: migrate full LNet NI information collection\")\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nChange-Id: Ie3a1e9c27132a28933f8546d774a85e83f8f247d\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61853\nReviewed-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\n"
